==English==
===Noun===
'''gunk'''
#(''uncountable'', ''informal'') [[dirt]] or [[grime]]; any vague or unknown substance
#:''I washed all the gunk off the light fixture, and found that it was white, not brown.''
2. A subculture of 21st century America, comprised of males, combining elements of Punk Rock and Modern Gothic lifestyles and dress.
3. Person of the Gunk subculture

